content.description:
A brief but very serious problem on good holds. Two half pad crimps suggest a match but they are separate incut crimps that make a lay down start with one decent right foot available. Throw hard and huge for a Topout jug.  

 There’s a lot of strong climbers but this silly dyno problem will only be put down by a real floater.One move wonder but there’s good holds and good landing to go all out.I personally wouldn’t hike out beyond Jug City for just this but if you’ve done the rest of the good probs in the area and want to flail on a 1 star hard problem then it’s just a few minutes away from the good stuff.
